6 September 2017Today the Minister of Communications, Ms Ayanda Dlodlo will deliver a keynote address during the Fourth Industrial Revolution High Level Dialogue today at 9h30. The dialogue is part of the programme of the SADC ICT Ministers s meeting currently underway at Fairmont Zimbali Resort in KwaZul-Natal. The meeting is co-hosted by the Department of Telecommunications and Postal Services as well as the Department of Communications starting from the 4th to the 8th of September 2017.Members of the media are invited to cover the session. The keynote address will be followed by a media briefing led by Minister Dlodlo and Minister Siyabonga Cwele. The details are:Date: Wednesday, 6 September 2017 Time: 13h00 Venue: Fairmont Zimbali Resort, Plenary Room.For further enquiries and interview requests contact: Pheliswa Sebati Cell: 082 413 4609Siya Qoza Cell: 082 898 1657